nicity\ndistributions, smaller-scale rotational motions are inferred within forming and\nevolving condensations. Upon the complete condensation of a prominence\n`monolith', the slow descent of this plasma towards lower heights appears\nconsistent with the mass-slippage mechanism driven by episodes of both local\ncurrent diffusion and magnetic reconnection.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 26 Nov 2020 18:34:05 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-02-24"}
