^{-1}}$, but the\nionised phase dominates at lower SFRs. Galaxies above solar metallicity exhibit\nlower ${\\rm L_{[C II]}}$/SFR ratios for the neutral phase. In comparison, the\n${\\rm L_{[C II]}}$/SFR ratio in the DIG is stable when metallicity varies. We\nsuggest that the reduced size of the neutral clouds, caused by increased SFRs,\nis the likely cause for the ${\\rm L_{[C II]}}$ deficit at high infrared\nluminosities, although EAGLE simulations do not reach these luminosities at\n$z=0$.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 26 Nov 2020 18:57:07 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-01-27"}
