anofabrication approach is critical to arriving at realistic geometric models\nto establish meaningful correlation between structure, optical properties and\nsensitivity of nanopillar arrays in plasmonic assays. The findings emphasize\nthe need for the rational design of EM hot-spots that take into account the\nanalyte dimensions to drive ultra-high sensitivity in plasmon-enhanced\nspectroscopies.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 27 Nov 2020 12:48:14 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-11-30"}
