istance\nto the star. The model predicts that the features and adjacent continuum are\ndue to different combinations of grain sub-populations, with a dependence on\nthe UV field intensity. Shorter wavelength features are dominated by the\nsmallest grains (< 0.7nm) throughout the disk, while at longer wavelengths what\ndominates the emission close to the star is a mix of several grain populations,\nand far away from the star is the largest nano-grain population.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 27 Nov 2020 15:12:53 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-05-19"}
